From 3e56a12165728eef7f5c06f4d09120b56af7e7a7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:40:09 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] sdl3: rename SDLK_<lowercase letter> to SDLK_<uppercase
 letter>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SDL3 renamed the lowercase-letter keysyms (SDLK_a..SDLK_z) to their
uppercase forms (SDLK_A..SDLK_Z). SDL3's <SDL3/SDL_oldnames.h> emits
deliberate compile canaries for the SDL2 spelling — e.g. defining
`SDLK_z` to expand to the undeclared identifier `SDLK_z_renamed_SDLK_Z`
so that consumers using the SDL2 name get a compiler error pointing
directly at the SDL3 name. Phase 5 attempt 5 surfaced 9 such canary
errors in src/input.cpp; this commit converts all 9 sites.

Default Cave Story bindings preserved: Z=jump, X=fire, C=strafe,
A=prev weapon, S=next weapon, Q=inventory, W=map system, B=frame
advance (debug), V=fly mode (debug). Keysym values are unchanged
(still ASCII codepoints) — only the C identifier moved.

This patch belongs to the SDL3 migration extension series (slot 0022,
following 0021's #include path normalization). 0010's mechanical-
renames covered SDL_RenderCopy / SDL_FreeSurface / etc. function-
renames but its regex targeted function identifiers, not enum values
inside expressions; this slot fills that gap.

No new SDL3-rename canaries surfaced in a broader audit
(`grep -rE 'SDLK_[a-z]\b' src/`); the 9 input.cpp sites were the
complete surface.

Authored-by: sdl-engine
Co-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/input.cpp | 25 ++++++++++++++++---------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/input.cpp b/src/input.cpp
index 95981b4..e6e352a 100644
--- a/src/input.cpp
+++ b/src/input.cpp
@@ -39,13 +39,19 @@ bool input_init(void)
   mappings[RIGHTKEY].key     = SDLK_RIGHT;
   mappings[UPKEY].key        = SDLK_UP;
   mappings[DOWNKEY].key      = SDLK_DOWN;
-  mappings[JUMPKEY].key      = SDLK_z;
-  mappings[FIREKEY].key      = SDLK_x;
-  mappings[STRAFEKEY].key    = SDLK_c;
-  mappings[PREVWPNKEY].key   = SDLK_a;
-  mappings[NEXTWPNKEY].key   = SDLK_s;
-  mappings[INVENTORYKEY].key = SDLK_q;
-  mappings[MAPSYSTEMKEY].key = SDLK_w;
+  // SDL3: lowercase letter keysyms (SDLK_a..SDLK_z) renamed to uppercase
+  // (SDLK_A..SDLK_Z). SDL3's SDL_oldnames.h emits a deliberate compile
+  // canary `SDLK_z_renamed_SDLK_Z` etc. for the SDL2 spelling so the
+  // compiler points consumers directly at the SDL3 name. Default Cave
+  // Story bindings: Z=jump, X=fire, A/S=prev/next weapon, etc. — values
+  // are unchanged (still ASCII codepoints), only the C identifier moved.
+  mappings[JUMPKEY].key      = SDLK_Z;
+  mappings[FIREKEY].key      = SDLK_X;
+  mappings[STRAFEKEY].key    = SDLK_C;
+  mappings[PREVWPNKEY].key   = SDLK_A;
+  mappings[NEXTWPNKEY].key   = SDLK_S;
+  mappings[INVENTORYKEY].key = SDLK_Q;
+  mappings[MAPSYSTEMKEY].key = SDLK_W;
 
   mappings[ESCKEY].key = SDLK_ESCAPE;
 
@@ -95,8 +101,9 @@ bool input_init(void)
   mappings[F11KEY].key = SDLK_F11;
   mappings[F12KEY].key = SDLK_F12;
   mappings[FREEZE_FRAME_KEY].key  = SDLK_SPACE;
-  mappings[FRAME_ADVANCE_KEY].key = SDLK_b;
-  mappings[DEBUG_FLY_KEY].key     = SDLK_v;
+  // SDL3: SDLK_b → SDLK_B, SDLK_v → SDLK_V (see comment above).
+  mappings[FRAME_ADVANCE_KEY].key = SDLK_B;
+  mappings[DEBUG_FLY_KEY].key     = SDLK_V;
   mappings[ENTERKEY].key = SDLK_RETURN;
 
   SDL_InitSubSystem(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK);
